EC2-PROJECT

Deploy a Web Application to Amazon ECS with EC2, Docker, ECR, Load balancer


PRACTICAL STEPS 

Create an instance in AWS ec2-server
ssh into the instance on linux
change to root user ( Sudo su)
download docker for linux(depending on your OS)

start docker with systemctl start docker
check the status  systemctl status docker- make sure it shows Active running status

Build a Centos image with Dockerfile and index.html files containerizing using docker and Deployment to Amazon ECS
create an Amazon ECR  and push the image to it

then create a loadbalancer to balance 
